1
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,760
Why isn't Lin You back yet?

2
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:16,080
It's so cold out there.

3
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:18,680
And the forecast said it'd rain today.

4
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,400
He didn't even bring an umbrella.

5
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:23,520
With that scrawny build of his...

6
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:24,440
He'll be fine.

7
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:25,000
Don't worry.

8
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:36,560
Liu Liu.

9
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:38,840
You've reheated that tea a hundred times.

10
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,040
Just sit down and wait.

11
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,680
Lin You will definitely be okay.

12
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,920
Mainly, he went alone again this time.

13
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,120
What if...

14
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:49,560
What if he...

15
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:51,040
What if something happens?

16
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:52,880
You'll get used to it.

17
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,360
If only Yao Yao were here.

18
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,200
That way,

19
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,160
he wouldn't have to go alone.

20
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:14,680
Lin You!

21
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:15,880
You're back!

22
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,320
Lin You.

23
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,360
Here's some ginger tea.

24
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,080
Drink up.

25
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,000
Warm yourself up.

26
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,520
It's okay, no rush.

27
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,680
Take your time and tell us.

28
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,560
Bro Bai sent me to wait for your update.

29
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:36,000
Did you...

30
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,400
stay up all night again?

31
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,520
Ever since I moved into this building,

32
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,800
I haven't seen a single child.

33
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,720
No children at all.

34
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,920
Because when I was pregnant,

35
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,440
I'd get hungry at night.

36
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,040
So at home,

37
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,240
I kept some snacks and biscuits around.

38
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,920
But I always felt like

39
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,640
they were disappearing really fast.

40
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,680
Granny.

41
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,960
I'm sorry, I'm sorry!

42
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:57,240
I'm sorry, I'm sorry!

43
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:58,760
I was just curious.

44
00:03:58,880 --> 00:03:59,840
Just taking a peek.

45
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,320
Granny, I've already apologized!

46
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:03,840
Granny!

47
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,000
Granny!

48
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,480
Granny!

49
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:08,760
Granny!

50
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,640
That old lady

51
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:25,120
is probably keeping a Little Wraith.

52
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,280
When you mentioned the cameras yesterday,

53
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,360
I started getting suspicious.

54
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,240
And now,

55
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,880
I'm pretty much certain.

56
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,680
When I was young, I went out with Lao Wang

57
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,920
and read a book

58
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,360
called the Compendium of Wraiths.

59
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,760
It mentioned a type called Little Wraith,

60
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,160
also known as a Child Wraith.

61
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:46,400
They're children who died young

62
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,120
and refused to move on.

63
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,280
Because they're so young,

64
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,280
they're really playful and mischievous.

65
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,480
And also

66
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,480
afraid of being alone.

67
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,600
But these little things are harmless.

68
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:01,760
They steal food to give to their Keeper.

69
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:02,880
And the Keeper

70
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,160
must accept the food.

71
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,600
It's sort of

72
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,600
like a pact, you could say.

73
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,000
That matches what the old lady is doing.

74
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:15,000
And from what you said,

75
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:16,640
outside her door,

76
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,760
she has several pothos plants.

77
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:21,840
What's wrong with pothos?

78
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,040
Aren't they really common?

79
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,880
Yes, they are common,

80
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,040
but it depends on the context.

81
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,480
At the old lady's place, it's not normal.

82
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,440
Have you heard the saying?

83
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,000
What saying?

84
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:39,320
One pothos plant, seven lost souls.

85
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:41,560
She's housing a Reinforced company.

86
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,520
That old lady

87
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,160
keeps evil spirits to hurt people!

88
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:55,760
I'm gonna...

89
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:56,760
Lin You.

90
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,840
What are you doing?

91
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:58,880
I'm going to confront her!

92
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,040
Lin You, hold on.

93
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,720
Just hear me out.

94
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:04,640
Go on.

95
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,240
This morning, Granny Sun

96
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,960
handed you an umbrella.

97
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,800
What does that tell us?

98
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,160
It tells us

99
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:16,880
she wants to hurt me.

100
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:25,520
The forecast said heavy rain today.

101
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:30,000
Here's what I think.

102
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:33,560
I think Granny Sun was just

103
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,280
worried you'd get soaked.

104
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,640
Think about it.

105
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:42,560
If someone wanted to hurt another person,

106
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,200
would she

107
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:46,080
ever do something

108
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,400
this thoughtful?

109
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,120
Also,

110
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:58,120
out of all the residents in the building,

111
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:01,200
why would she target Sis Xiaobai?

112
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,880
It doesn't make sense.

113
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:08,920
So,

114
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:12,760
even if Granny Sun keeps a Little Wraith,

115
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,120
I don't think

116
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,480
she means to hurt anyone.

117
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,960
So what do we do?

118
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,400
Anyway,

119
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,720
right now it's just a suspicion

120
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,400
that Granny Sun keeps a Little Wraith.

121
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:35,120
We need to confirm it first

122
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,320
before we can find a breakthrough.

123
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,920
So,

124
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,440
Lin You,

125
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,040
please.

126
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:50,840
I'm counting on you.

127
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,560
When under another's roof,

128
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:09,800
you have to bow your head.

129
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:11,680
For Sis Xiaobai's sake.

130
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,320
Lin You.

131
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,520
What?

132
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,200
Are you still scared?

133
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,720
It's just a Little Wraith.

134
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,000
Why are you scared of a kid?

135
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:35,840
Kid or not,

136
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,480
he's still an evil spirit!

137
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:40,360
It'll be fine.

138
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,679
I believe in you, Flashbang.

139
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:45,120
Hang copper coins in the hallway too.

140
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,680
Otherwise, we can't confirm if it's her.

141
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,720
Good night.

142
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,080
Damn you, Zhou Yi!

143
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:01,800
Zhou Yi!

144
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:04,200
You just wait!

145
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,600
Bastard!

146
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:26,000
You okay?

147
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:36,160
I'm in position.

148
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:37,440
Over.

149
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:44,040
Guess my worrying was unnecessary.

150
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:47,040
Lin You's really getting the hang of this.

151
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,120
Thanks, guys.

152
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:56,840
Lin You.

153
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,080
You should get a new phone.

154
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,800
This method's way too old-school.

155
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:02,440
Over.

156
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,080
Keep the talisman paper close to you.

157
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,480
It's almost time.

158
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,000
The kid came out.

159
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,200
From Granny Sun's place.

160
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:42,960
I'm sure of it.

161
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:47,880
Here it comes.

162
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,760
Right here with me.

163
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:12,640
Granny Sun.

164
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:13,840
Granny Sun.

165
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,000
Granny Sun.

166
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,720
We're from Lucky Realty.

167
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:18,800
We just came by today...

168
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:24,840
Don't I look handsome?

169
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:40,560
Granny.

170
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:42,880
Granny Sun.

171
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,120
Granny.

172
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,400
We were wrong to raise our voices.

173
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:02,920
We just worried you couldn't hear us.

174
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,040
Keeping an evil spirit makes you right?

175
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,040
Let me tell you...

176
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:06,760
Don't stop me.

177
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:07,680
This is twice now.

178
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:08,720
I've had enough!

179
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:09,640
Wait a minute...

180
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:10,800
You think you're in the right?

181
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:11,400
Okay, okay, okay.

182
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:12,760
Granny.

183
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:14,680
The Tao Te Ching says:

184
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,240
"Heaven's way is impartial,

185
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:17,640
yet it always sides with the good."

186
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:18,400
And this one:

187
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:20,520
"Nature says few words.

188
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:22,800
A fierce wind doesn't last all morning,

189
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:25,400
and a sudden rain doesn't last all day."

190
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:28,000
"Who makes it so?"

191
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:29,840
Granny.

192
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:32,080
The Tao Te Ching also says...

193
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,120
Hold on, let me turn the page.

194
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:34,760
I...

195
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:43,600
What are you doing?

196
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,280
Why are you pulling me?

197
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,040
Auntie Sun.

198
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:57,720
Auntie Sun.

199
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:00,440
Auntie Sun.

200
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,480
I'm begging you.

201
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:05,080
Please stop making a scene in the hall.

202
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,800
We're a small company.

203
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:09,320
Buying from the developer wasn't easy.

204
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,520
Auntie Sun.

205
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:15,360
Auntie Sun.

206
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:17,760
Auntie Sun, please.

207
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:20,520
We went through a lot to renovate it.

208
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,800
We barely make any money selling a unit.

209
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:25,640
You're stinking up the hallway all day.

210
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:27,760
It scares away all the potential buyers.

211
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,720
We've all got families to support.

212
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:31,040
It's not easy, you know?

213
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:32,600
Auntie Sun.

214
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,000
I'm begging you.

215
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:35,320
Please have some mercy.

216
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,560
Give it a rest, won't you?

217
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:48,160
Auntie Sun.

218
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:49,480
Remember that!

219
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:52,360
Let's go.

220
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,400
That old lady...

221
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:04,960
sure knows how to make enemies.

222
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:08,440
Why are you hiding?
